§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Given a family of topological spaces $ℱ = \set{(X_α, 𝒯_α}_{α
    ∈ I}$, the ❬product topology❭ of $ℱ$ is the topology on
    $∏_{α ∈ I} X_α$ generated by the set
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ \Set*{ p_{β}^{-1}(U_β)) }{ (∃β)(U_β ∈ X_{β}) } ⦉
    ⦉
    where $p_β: ∏_{α ∈ I} X_α → X_β$ is the ␣
    <a href='/sheets/direct_products.html'>
      ‖ $β$ coordinate projection. ⦉
    </a>⦉

  ‖ Some authorities also use the terminology ❬Tychonoff topology❭. ⦉
⦉

